The paper deals with parametricity theory and its application in dependently-typed programming languages, which are topics related to logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the implementation of the translation as Coq programs, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE). The use of reification and reflection in the implementation suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper mentions free theorems, which are related to formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
